properties.otherAdvice:

Residents will be permitted past closure points but cannot travel across the bridge.
properties.diversions:

*Note Charleys Forrest Rd is also closed and cannot be used as a detour route.

Heavy vehicles should use the Kings Hwy, or other approved routes depending on their load limit restriction.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Oversize vehicle - BERRY TO BOMADERRY Princes Highway
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Motorists are advised of an oversized delivery of bridge girders which will be delivered in the early hours to minimise the impact on highway for the Princes Hwy upgrade.

The 12 girders, which are 31m long, 2.1m wide and weigh approximately 50 tonnes each.

The police and escort vehicles will control traffic along the route which includes intermittent lane closures and side streets to allow for a safe passage for the oversize truck to pass. Motorists are advised to drive to the conditions and follow the directions of signs and traffic control.

properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - Saturday 22 to Monday 24 February - SURRY HILLS Chalmers Street between Cleveland Street, Chippendale AND Devonshire Street
properties.otherAdvice:
Special event clearways will be in place on both sides of Chalmers St between Cleveland St and Devonshire St from 2am Sat 22 Feb to 2am Mon 24 Mar. This is to accommodate bussing operations to replace train services as a result of Sydney trains track work.

Clearways are strictly no parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.
